&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GUY’S AND ST. THOMAS’ HOSPITAL NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Clinical Fellow in Endoscopy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nodal Point – 4 - £49,036 p.a excl. LZ&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time - 40 hrs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term – 12 months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Senior Endoscopy Fellow post for twelve months at Guy’s and St Thomas’ hospital. This post is designed to both deliver high quality endoscopic care and allow training in advanced endoscopic techniques. This will help in furthering a career in gastroenterology with an interest in endoscopy and is available to applicants who want to take time out of programme or for post CCT candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to join a dynamic gastroenterology team in a highly supportive environment. The successful candidates would contribute to the provision of endoscopic services for both in and outpatients and contribute to the gastroenterology bleed on call rota (1 in 8). Within their endoscopy service commitments, the post holder would also be expected to provide occasional support to the endoscopy service across the SEL region. This would involve providing occasional adhoc support for endoscopy sessions at KCH (King’s College Hospital and Lewisham and Greenwich Hospital). There are no general medical on call commitments in this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a wide range of endoscopic services to inpatients and outpatients. We have a varied portfolio of tertiary endoscopy services, including endoscopic ultrasound, cyst gastrostomy, oesophageal and colonic endotherapy (e.g. HALO RFA, endoscopic mucosal resections, complex colonic polypectomies), tertiary pancreato-biliary procedures, capsule endoscopy an oesophageal physiology. The successful candidates will be given opportunities to train in one or more of these advanced endoscopic techniques depending on their requirements/preference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and to apply online, please go to our website quoting reference number &lt;strong&gt;MED2216.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 22nd November 2020, at midnight&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an organisation we are committed to developing our services in ways that best suit the needs of our patients. This means that some staff groups will increasingly be asked to work a more flexible shift pattern so that we can offer services in the evenings or at weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All our vacancies can be viewed on our website.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our excellent benefits include final salary pension scheme. Please visit our website to find out more.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Equality of opportunity is our Policy. The Trust provides health services to a diverse community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that successful completion of the International English Language Testing System (IELTS) is our accepted minimum language requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details/informal visits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical lead: Dr Giovanni Tritto at Giovanni.tritto@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Lead: Dr Joel Mawdsley at joel.mawdsley@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Endoscopy Lead: Dr Jason Dunn at Jason.dunn@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy General Manager: Aaron Horner at Aaron.horner@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
